Sentencas: To improve thermal expansion compatibility and structural stability of the cobalt-based double perovskite cathode such as GdBaCo2O5+delta, a cobalt-free double perovskite GdBaFeNiO5+delta (GBFN) is investigated as a potential cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells based on Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 (SDC) electrolyte.
Titulo: Cobalt-free double perovskite cathode GdBaFeNiO5+δ and electrochemical performance improvement by Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 impregnation for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The structure, properties and improved electrochemical performance of the GBFN material are reported in detail.
Titulo: Cobalt-free double perovskite cathode GdBaFeNiO5+δ and electrochemical performance improvement by Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 impregnation for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The GBFN has a tetragonal structure at room temperature.
Titulo: Cobalt-free double perovskite cathode GdBaFeNiO5+δ and electrochemical performance improvement by Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 impregnation for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Mixed valence states of Fe3+/Fe4+ and Ni2+/Ni3+ coexist in the GBFN material.
Titulo: Cobalt-free double perovskite cathode GdBaFeNiO5+δ and electrochemical performance improvement by Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 impregnation for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The absence of spin state in Ni2+ contributes to a reduction in the thermal expansion coefficient (TEC).
Titulo: Cobalt-free double perovskite cathode GdBaFeNiO5+δ and electrochemical performance improvement by Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 impregnation for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The average TEC of the GBFN sample is 14.7 x 10(-6) K-1 between 30 and 1000 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Cobalt-free double perovskite cathode GdBaFeNiO5+δ and electrochemical performance improvement by Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 impregnation for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The GBFN undergoes a transition from semiconductor to metallically conductive behaviors at 400 degrees C.
Titulo: Cobalt-free double perovskite cathode GdBaFeNiO5+δ and electrochemical performance improvement by Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 impregnation for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The substitution of Fe and Ni for Co significantly improves the structural stability of the GBFN.
Titulo: Cobalt-free double perovskite cathode GdBaFeNiO5+δ and electrochemical performance improvement by Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 impregnation for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The GBFN material exhibits a good chemical compatibility with SDC electrolyte at temperatures below 1000 degrees C.
Titulo: Cobalt-free double perovskite cathode GdBaFeNiO5+δ and electrochemical performance improvement by Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 impregnation for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The activity and performance of the GBFN cathode are further improved by the impregnation of nano-sized SDC particles: the polarization resistance is decreased by similar to 14.2 times and the maximum power density of cell is increased by similar to 1.9 times.
Titulo: Cobalt-free double perovskite cathode GdBaFeNiO5+δ and electrochemical performance improvement by Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 impregnation for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The reason of electrochemical performance improvement is also discussed.
Titulo: Cobalt-free double perovskite cathode GdBaFeNiO5+δ and electrochemical performance improvement by Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 impregnation for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
